value.value: Non-heritable difficulty in distinguishing colors.
Genetic based difficulty in distinguishing colors.
Diminished clarity of vision.
Diminished clarity of vision despite optimal optical correction (glasses and/or contacts).
Diminished clarity of vision without optical correction (glasses and/or contacts).

value.value: Diminished clarity of vision with current correction (glasses and/or contacts).
Perception of two images secondary to misalignment of the eyes.
Perception of more than one image when viewing with one eye.

The separation of the vitreous from the retina.
An infection of one or more of the glands surrounding the eye.
Involuntary twitching of the eyelid.
The prominence of the superficial vessels of the sclera or conjunctiva resulting in a red or pink appearance.
A separation of the iris from the ciliary body.
The false appearance of misalignment of the eyes.

Reduced or abnormal sight in the central visual field.
Identically shaped visual field defect in the same location in both eyes.

value.value: A question about whether an individual has or had been told by other people that they seem to have trouble remembering information.
Lack of sight in half of the normal field of vision.
A bilateral visual field defect on opposite sides of the visual space of each eye (right or left).
A bilateral visual field defect on the same side of visual space of each eye (right or left).
Non-identically shaped visual field defect in the same location in both eyes.

value.value: A question about whether an individual has or had been told by other people that they seem to have trouble speaking clearly.
Reduced or abnormal sight in the peripheral visual field.

label.value: Have Been Told that I Seem Confused

label.value: Have Been Able to Pay Attention and Keep Track of What I am Doing Without Extra Effort

value.value: A question about whether an individual is or was able to pay attention and keep track of what they are doing without extra effort.
